<p>Is this satire? Because I really don&#8217;t see how it could be anything else, except perhaps insanity.</p>

<p>The problem with providing these sorts of benefits to everyone is that it removes nearly all extrinsic motivations for work. Unfortunately, I believe that you&#8217;ll find that the fraction of the human population that is intrinsically motivated to work is by no means large enough to support the entire population&#8212;and if this is the case, then the reforms you propose would eventually cause the collapse of civilization (assuming that someone did not eventually stop the madness).</p>

